@ballcap231 has a point, epochs is not the same thing as time, is there any way to maybe add a callback "on_epoch_end" to check the elapsed time?

Maybe somethign like adding [here](https://github.com/uber/ludwig/blob/ee4d5daf07fda2168c4e89dd962b151506d17f9a/ludwig/models/model.py#L482):

```
while progress_tracker.epoch < self.epochs OR elapsed_time > allowed_time:
```
